<item>
            <title>[JOHNZON-164] Non Spec conform handling of illegal json</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JOHNZON-164</link>
                <project id="12315523" key="JOHNZON">Johnzon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we receive wrong information (e.g. an illegal Base64 encoded byte[]) then we currently throw an IllegalArgumentException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following behaviour is defined in the specifications:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the JSON-B spec we should throw a JsonbException&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://static.javadoc.io/javax.json.bind/javax.json.bind-api/1.0/index.html?javax/json/bind/annotation/package-summary.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://static.javadoc.io/javax.json.bind/javax.json.bind-api/1.0/index.html?javax/json/bind/annotation/package-summary.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If native JSON-P is being used we should throw a JsonParsingException&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/json/JsonReader.html#read--&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/json/JsonReader.html#read--&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
